cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper is about compressing and accelerating convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves fine-tuning the pruned models, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed entropy-based method for evaluating filter importance is a novel contribution, which could be of interest to researchers in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which could also fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
